description:

Note: Your holder can be customized with your business logo!

Available in a multitude of wood options. 

Grain and finish may vary with each piece—that’s the best part about wood goods. 

Please contact me for more detailed International shipping options/prices or custom sized boxes.

name: Paul Bunyan Block Bot
description:
After what seems like several lifetimes of swinging his giant axe and living large among the evergreens, Paulie B. is ready to come indoors. Call it a crisis of philosophy with his new, treehugging ways, but his fashion sense will permanently remain in the plaid-shirt-and-jeans camp. Paul also wants you to know he’s the perfect pal to share a beer and a tall tale—and he won’t touch a leaf on any of the trees in your yard if you find a spot for him in your home. (He’s hoping that Oh Dier and screenprinter/graphic designer extraordinaire Nate Johannes, who helped bring him to life, will follow up with a re-creation of his trusty pal, Babe.)

PS: While his legend is large, Paul’s actual measurements are 7.5" x 3.5" with each limb measuring 1.75" x 1.75". He weighs in at just under 3 lbs.

name: Proportional counting blocks
description:
These little numbered blocks make the perfect gift for your little one learning to count. Beautiful enough to display on a shelf, while able to endure years of play. The proportional sizes teach easy counting and adding (math without the workbooks!). Stack the one on top of the nine to make the same size as ten and so on and so forth.

• Each set includes blocks one through ten
• 1 5/8" x 1 5/8" x (1/4" - 2 1/2")
• This set is made from reclaimed maple sanded to smooth finish
• They can either be left in their raw state or finished with beeswax and cold pressed orange peel. Please specify which at checkout.

The blocks arrive ready to use in a cotton drawstring carrying bag, a thank you card from us, as well as care instructions to ensure your blocks look the same for your children's grandchildren as they do the day you receive them.

name: Custom Poem Deposit
description:
This work was created for the beginnings of our baby Ruby’s nursery —before we even knew she’d be a Ruby! Lasered into each block of oak is a line from the first poem Katie ever memorized.  Each line was then tied together with rope for a slightly nautical/preppy feel. Hung on the wall, it functions as a piece of art and a way to pass along Katie’s love of poetry and literature and William’s love of art and creating to Ruby—an heirloom. 

Got an inspirational quote or phrase? Poem or line from your favorite piece of literature? A verse from the Bible or your favorite rock and roll song?

Let us know what inspires you and we can get started creating a custom piece that will become your own heirloom. 

Pricing varies depending on size and materials; email us for an estimate. The $25 deposit covers the design of the sign and will go towards the final purchase price.

description:
Captain Blockbeard, lives on the open sea and mans the Queen Anne's Revenge. After a career of ransoming and raiding he wants a quieter life, and with that, a new matey. If you are interested, and do not mind the smell of freshly sharpened pencils and a few choice words every now and then, please give him a call.

While the lore of Blockbeard is quite large, his body measurements are only 7.5" x 3.5" with each limb being 1.75" x 1.75" He is made out of recycled wood from an old newel post and has very smooth skin without that oily, stinky finish other pirates often have.

name: William Woodsworth Bot
description:
William Woodsworth, or as his friends call him Woody, lives in a small bungalow and teaches Historical Survey on British Literature at a local liberal arts college. John Keats, Elizabeth Barrett Browning and T. S. Eliot are a few of his favorite authors. His guilty pleasures include sing-a-long sessions in his vintage VW to lady gaga and low budget late night infomercials.

While Woody has a big heart, and brain for that matter, his body measurements are only 7" x 3". He is made out of recycled wood from old buildings and/or reclaimed centers and has very smooth skin without that oily finish other bots may have. 

Since Woody does not like to be eaten, he would be unsafe for households with small children who like to place small items in their mouths. 

William is looking for a change in his life and would love to find a new roommate. If you are interested, and do not mind the smell of freshly sharpened pencils, please give him a call.
